.TH NMDNS 1 "April 2026" "nmdns 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.
.SH NAME
nmdns \- mDNS / DNS\-SD responder, cache, and cross\-interface repeater
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nmdns
.RB [ \-f ]
.RB [ \-c
.IR config ]
.br
.B nmdns
.B \-\-check
.RB [ \-c
.IR config ]
.br
.B nmdns
.B \-h
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B nmdns
is a daemon for Linux hosts that sit between multiple link\-local
network segments (routers, gateways, VLANs, container bridges, etc.).
It performs four functions:
.
.TP
.B Cache
Every DNS resource record seen on any interface is parsed and stored
with its TTL.  The cache is used internally for diagnostics and TTL
tracking; the daemon does not currently answer queries on the wire
from cache contents (only from records it publishes itself).
.
.TP
.B Respond
Answers
.BR A ,
.BR PTR ,
.BR SRV ,
and
.B TXT
queries for the host\(aqs own
.I <hostname>.local.\&
name and any DNS\-SD services declared in the configuration file.
At startup the daemon probes for its names (RFC\ 6762\ \(sc8.1),
then announces all records twice (RFC\ 6762\ \(sc8.3).
On shutdown it sends goodbye packets with TTL\ =\ 0 twice
(RFC\ 6762\ \(sc10.1).
.
.TP
.B Browse
Periodically sends
.B PTR
queries for configured service types so the cache remains warm for
clients that never issue their own queries.  Query intervals follow
the exponential back\-off required by RFC\ 6762\ \(sc5.2.
.
.TP
.B Repeat
Optionally re\-multicasts raw mDNS frames between interfaces so
legacy clients that speak mDNS directly (rather than querying a cache)
can still discover devices on other segments.
.
.PP
Because mDNS uses link\-local multicast with IP\ TTL\ =\ 1, a standard
Layer\-3 router drops these packets at the segment boundary.
.B nmdns
bridges the gap without requiring any changes to clients or services.
.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-c " config"
Path to the TOML configuration file.
Default:
.IR /etc/nmdns.toml .
.
.TP
.B \-f
Run in the foreground and write log messages to
.B stderr
instead of syslog.
.
.TP
.B \-\-check
Parse and validate the configuration file, print a summary, then exit.
See
.B EXIT STATUS
for error codes.
.
.TP
.B \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a short usage summary and exit.
.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.
.TP
.B 2
Command\-line usage error emitted by
.BR clap .
.
.TP
.B 10
Configuration file load, parse, or structural validation failed.
.
.TP
.B 11
Semantic
.B \-\-check
validation failed, such as an invalid DNS name.
.
.TP
.B 12
Another daemon appears to be running from the PID file.
.
.TP
.B 13
Daemonization or PID file setup failed.
.
.TP
.B 14
Tokio runtime creation failed.
.
.TP
.B 20
Network interface/socket setup failed.
.
.TP
.B 21
Privilege drop failed.
.
.TP
.B 22
Service record construction failed during runtime startup.
.
.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file uses
.BR TOML (5)
syntax.  An annotated example is installed at
.IR /usr/share/doc/nmdns/nmdns.toml .
.
.SS Top\-level keys
.TP
.B interfaces
.RI "(list of strings, required)"
Network interface names the daemon listens and responds on.
At least one must be specified.
.
.TP
.B repeat
.RI "(bool, default: " true ")"
Forward unparsed mDNS frames between interfaces.
Set to
.B false
for pure responder\-only operation.
.
.TP
.B hostname
.RI "(string, default: system hostname)"
The bare hostname advertised as
.IR hostname .local.
on every interface.
.
.TP
.B blacklist
.RI "(list of CIDR strings, default: " [] ")"
Drop all traffic whose source IP falls within any listed subnet.
Mutually exclusive with
.BR whitelist .
.
.TP
.B whitelist
.RI "(list of CIDR strings, default: " [] ")"
Only accept traffic whose source IP falls within a listed subnet.
Mutually exclusive with
.BR blacklist .
.
.TP
.B browse
.RI "(list of DNS names, default: " ["_services._dns-sd._udp.local."] ")"
Service types the daemon actively queries for.  The default discovers
every DNS\-SD service type advertised on the link (RFC\ 6763\ \(sc9).
Example of a narrower target:
.IR _http._tcp.local. .
.
.TP
.B browse_interval_secs
.RI "(integer, default: " 60 ")"
Upper bound on the exponential back\-off interval between successive
browse queries, in seconds.
.
.TP
.B cache_tick_secs
.RI "(integer, default: " 5 ")"
How often (in seconds) the cache eviction sweep runs to remove
records whose TTL has expired.
.
.TP
.B max_cache_entries
.RI "(integer, default: " 4096 ")"
Upper bound on the number of records held in the cache.  When full,
the nearest\-to\-expiry entry is evicted to make room for an insert.
.
.TP
.B foreground
.RI "(bool, default: " false ")"
Same as the
.B \-f
flag.
.
.TP
.B pid_file
.RI "(string, default: " /run/nmdns.pid ")"
Path to the PID file written when the daemon is running in the
background.
.
.TP
.B user
.RI "(string, default: none)"
Unix user name the daemon drops privileges to after binding sockets.
.
.SS Service tables
Each
.B [[service]]
block publishes one DNS\-SD instance and accepts the following keys:
.
.TP
.B name
.RI "(string, required)"
Human\-readable instance name, e.g.\&
.IR "Office Printer" .
.
.TP
.B service
.RI "(string, required)"
DNS\-SD service type, e.g.\&
.IR _ipp._tcp.local. .
.
.TP
.B port
.RI "(integer 1\(en65535, required)"
TCP or UDP port advertised in the
.B SRV
record.
.
.TP
.B txt
.RI "(list of strings, default: " [] ")"
Key=value pairs placed in the
.B TXT
record, e.g.\&
.IR "rp=ipp/print" .
.
.TP
.B host
.RI "(string, default: daemon hostname)"
Override the target hostname in the
.B SRV
record.
.
.SH RFC 6762 COMPLIANCE
The following rules are implemented and each is covered by a dedicated
test in
.IR tests/rfc6762.rs .
.
.TS
tab(@) allbox;
lb lb lb
l l l.
RFC \(sc@Rule@Status
\(sc3@Hostnames are <single-label>.local.@\(OK
\(sc5.2@Browser: 20\(en120 ms initial jitter@\(OK
\(sc5.2@Browser: exponential back\-off, doubling each query@\(OK
\(sc6@Unique answer / probe\-defense: respond without delay@\(OK
\(sc6@Shared / multi\-question: 20\(en120 ms randomized delay@\(OK
\(sc6@TC bit set on query: 400\(en500 ms randomized delay@\(OK
\(sc6@Per\-(record, interface) 1 s minimum multicast interval@\(OK
\(sc6@Probe\-defense uses 250 ms interval@\(OK
\(sc7.1@Known\-Answer Suppression (TTL >= 50%% rule)@\(OK
\(sc8.1@Probe: 0\(en250 ms initial random jitter@\(OK
\(sc8.1@Probe: three probes 250 ms apart@\(OK
\(sc8.1@Probe message format (qtype=ANY, QU bit, Authority Section)@\(OK
\(sc8.1@Detect incoming probes via Authority Section@\(OK
\(sc8.3@Announcement gap >= 1 s@\(OK
\(sc10.1@Goodbye: TTL=0 on host A and service PTR/SRV/TXT@\(OK
\(sc10.1@Receiver: TTL=0 deletes the cached record@\(OK
\(sc10.2@Cache\-flush bit on unique records only (not shared PTR)@\(OK
\(sc11@Source\-address filter (CIDR blacklist / whitelist)@\(OK
\(sc11@IP TTL=255 on outgoing mDNS sockets@\(OK
\(sc18.4@Authoritative Answer bit set on responses@\(OK
\(sc8.2@Simultaneous\-probe tiebreaking / rename\-on\-conflict@\(em
\(sc6.1@NSEC negative responses@\(em
\(sc7.2@Multi\-packet Known\-Answer aggregation@\(em
.TE
.
.PP
Run
.B cargo test \-\-test rfc6762
to execute the compliance suite.
.
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGTERM ", " SIGINT
Graceful shutdown: send goodbye packets (TTL\ =\ 0) on every interface,
then exit.
.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/nmdns.toml
Default configuration file.
.
.TP
.I /run/nmdns.pid
Default PID file (when running as a daemon).
.
.SH EXAMPLES
Respond for the host's own name and two services on two interfaces:
.
.RS 4
.EX
interfaces = ["br\-lan", "br\-iot"]
hostname   = "gateway"

[[service]]
name    = "Web UI"
service = "_http._tcp.local."
port    = 80
txt     = ["path=/"]

[[service]]
name    = "SSH"
service = "_ssh._tcp.local."
port    = 22
.EE
.RE
.
.PP
Validate the config and exit:
.
.RS 4
.EX
nmdns \-\-check \-c /etc/nmdns.toml
.EE
.RE
.
.SH NOTES
.B nmdns
must start with sufficient privilege to bind UDP port\ 5353 and join
multicast groups.  Either run as
.B root
or grant
.BR CAP_NET_BIND_SERVICE " and " CAP_NET_RAW .
After the sockets are bound the daemon drops to the user specified in
.BR user .
.
.PP
IPv6 mDNS (address
.IR ff02::fb )
is not currently implemented.
.
